'''Fcitx''' (Free Chinese Input Toy for X) <nowiki>[ˈfaɪtɪks]</nowiki> is an input method framework with extension support.

== Installation ==
You can install Fcitx by using the following command:
{{Emerge|app-i18n/fcitx}}

=== Use Flags ===
{{USEflag|package=app-i18n/fcitx
|cairo+yes+yes
|debug
|gtk++yes+Install GTK2 IM module
|gtk3+++Install GTK3 IM module
|introspection
|lua
|opencc
|pango+yes+yes
|qt4++yes
|snooper
|static-libs
|table+yes++Adds support for table-based IM systems like Wubi, Erbi
}}

It is strongly recommended to add the gtk, gtk3 and qt4 useflags when you have applications using these toolkits.

== Using Fcitx ==
In order to use Fcitx in X, you need to add these environment variables (you need to <code>export</code> them after setting these variables):

If you use GDM, KDM or LightDM to login, add them to ~/.xprofile. If you use startx, SLiM, etc. to login, add them to ~/.xinitrc.

<pre>
XIM=fcitx
XIM_PROGRAM=fcitx
XMODIFIERS="@im=fcitx"
QT_IM_MODULE=<module>
GTK_IM_MODULE=<module>
</pre>

If you add gtk, gtk3 and qt4 to <code>USE</code>, &lt;module&gt; will be `fcitx', otherwise it should be `xim'.

It is recommended to start the [[D-Bus]] session bus before Fcitx starts.
Add these to the '''beginning''' of your X startup file (~/.xprofile or ~/.xinitrc):
<pre>
eval "$(dbus-launch --sh-syntax --exit-with-session)"
</pre>
<!--
Note: If you want to use Fcitx in English language, you may add <code>LC_CTYPE=zh_CN.UTF-8</code> in environment.
-->

Note: If you want to use Fcitx in X, your [[locale]] '''CANNOT''' be `C' or `POSIX'.

== Configuration ==
You can edit Fcitx's configuration file at <code>~/.config/fcitx/config</code>.

Also, there is a tool to configure Fcitx called {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-configtool}} (You may need to add the '~arch' keyword in package.accept_keywords to install it).

